thumbnails overhaul:

- fix mismatch between reported thumbnail size and on-disk image when both width & height are provided;
- width can now be optional if height is provided;
- introducing thumbnail operation modes: "fit" (default. requested width / height behave as maximum allowed dimensions), "crop" (replaces previous `crop` kwarg) and "stretch" (aspect ratio isn't preserved);
- thumbnail returns original image when it's smaller than the requested dimensions and new `upscale` kwarg is `False` (default in "fit" mode).

other implementation details / smaller fixes:

- `get_image_info` returns jpeg dimensions swapped when exif rotation is in effect;
- fix bug when image type is unknown;
- fix off-by-1px rounding discrepancy between reported thumbnail size and imagemagick output.
